    Class Description
    Collection
    The root interface in the collection hierarchy.
    CollectionAdapter
    A collection represents a group of objects, known as its elements.
    HashIteratorAdapter
    This class implements the Iterator interface.
    Iterator
    An iterator over a collection.
    List
    An ordered collection (also known as a sequence).
    ListAdapter
    This class implements the List interface, backed by a Vector instance.
    ListIterator
    An iterator for lists that allows the programmer to traverse the list in either direction, modify the list during iteration, and obtain the iterator's current position in the list.
    ListIteratorAdapter
    An iterator for lists that allows the programmer to traverse the list in either direction, modify the list during iteration, and obtain the iterator's current position in the list.
    Map
    An object that maps keys to values.
    Map.Entry
    A map entry (key-value pair).
    MapAdapter
    Vector implementation of the List interface, backed by a Hashtable instance.
    MyEntry
    This class is a really minimalist implementation of Map.Entry interface.
    Set
    A collection that contains no duplicate elements.
    SetAdapter
    This class implements the Set interface, backed by a hash table.
    VectorIteratorAdapter
    This class implements the Iterator interface.
